---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import HeadlineComponent from '../../components/Headline.astro';

const title = 'Headline';
const description =
  'WCAG AAA compliant heading component with enhanced typography, responsive design, and comprehensive accessibility features.';
---

<DocsLayout {title} {description}>
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <p class="text-base text-slate-100">
      Headline provides semantic heading elements with enhanced typography, WCAG
      AAA compliant colors, and responsive text sizing. Built for optimal
      readability and accessibility across all devices and screen readers.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      The component features comprehensive color variants, flexible sizing
      options, and intelligent text balancing for professional typography.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Props</h2>
    <dl class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          title?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Text content for the headline. Alternatively, use slot content.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          level?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Semantic heading level: <code>h1</code>, <code>h2</code>, <code
            >h3</code
          >, <code>h4</code>, <code>h5</code>, <code>h6</code>. Defaults to <code
            >h1</code
          >.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          textSize?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Responsive text size: <code>xs</code>, <code>sm</code>, <code
            >base</code
          >, <code>lg</code>, <code>xl</code>, <code>2xl</code>, <code>3xl</code
          >, <code>4xl</code>. Defaults to <code>lg</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          textAlign?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Text alignment: <code>left</code>, <code>center</code>, <code
            >right</code
          >, <code>justify</code>. Defaults to <code>left</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          color?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          WCAG AAA compliant colors: <code>default</code>, <code>muted</code>, <code
            >accent</code
          >, <code>success</code>, <code>warning</code>, <code>error</code>.
          Defaults to <code>default</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          weight?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Font weight: <code>normal</code>, <code>medium</code>, <code
            >semibold</code
          >, <code>bold</code>, <code>extrabold</code>. Defaults to <code
            >bold</code
          >.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          balance?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Enable text balancing for better line distribution. Defaults to <code
            >true</code
          >.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          maxWidth?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Maximum width: <code>none</code>, <code>sm</code>, <code>md</code>, <code
            >lg</code
          >, <code>xl</code>, <code>2xl</code>, <code>prose</code>. Defaults to <code
            >none</code
          >.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Usage</h2>
    <div
      class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
    >
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
        Import the Headline component and use it with semantic heading levels.
        The component automatically provides responsive typography and
        accessibility features.
      </p>
      <pre
        class="rounded bg-slate-950/50 p-4 text-sm text-slate-300 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`---
import Headline from '../../components/Headline.astro';
---

<Headline 
  level="h1" 
  textSize="2xl" 
  color="default"
  weight="bold"
>
  Main Page Title
</Headline>

<Headline 
  level="h2" 
  textSize="lg" 
  color="muted"
  textAlign="center"
>
  Section Subtitle
</Headline>`}</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Examples</h2>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div
        class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
      >
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Text Sizes</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          Responsive text sizing that adapts to different screen sizes.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded p-6 space-y-4">
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h2"
            textSize="xs"
            title="Extra Small Headline"
          />
          <HeadlineComponent level="h2" textSize="sm" title="Small Headline" />
          <HeadlineComponent level="h2" textSize="base" title="Base Headline" />
          <HeadlineComponent level="h2" textSize="lg" title="Large Headline" />
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h2"
            textSize="xl"
            title="Extra Large Headline"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
      >
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Color Variants</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          WCAG AAA compliant color variants for different contexts.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded p-6 space-y-3">
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            color="default"
            title="Default Text"
          />
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            color="muted"
            title="Muted Text"
          />
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            color="accent"
            title="Accent Text"
          />
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            color="success"
            title="Success Text"
          />
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            color="warning"
            title="Warning Text"
          />
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            color="error"
            title="Error Text"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
      >
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Font Weights</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          Different font weights for various design needs.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded p-6 space-y-3">
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            weight="normal"
            title="Normal Weight"
          />
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            weight="medium"
            title="Medium Weight"
          />
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            weight="semibold"
            title="Semibold Weight"
          />
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            weight="bold"
            title="Bold Weight"
          />
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            weight="extrabold"
            title="Extra Bold Weight"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
      >
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Text Alignment</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          Different alignment options for various layouts.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded p-6 space-y-4">
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            textAlign="left"
            title="Left Aligned Headline"
          />
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            textAlign="center"
            title="Center Aligned Headline"
          />
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            textAlign="right"
            title="Right Aligned Headline"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
      >
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Maximum Width</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          Constrained width for optimal reading experience.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded p-6 space-y-4">
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            maxWidth="prose"
            title="This headline has a maximum width of prose for optimal reading experience and better text layout"
          />
          <HeadlineComponent
            level="h3"
            textSize="base"
            maxWidth="lg"
            textAlign="center"
            title="This centered headline is constrained to large width"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Accessibility</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
        The Headline component implements comprehensive accessibility features:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-300 list-disc list-inside ml-4">
        <li>
          Semantic HTML heading elements (h1-h6) for proper document structure
        </li>
        <li>
          WCAG AAA contrast ratios (7:1+) for all color variants in light and
          dark modes
        </li>
        <li>
          Responsive typography that scales appropriately across all device
          sizes
        </li>
        <li>Text balancing for improved line distribution and readability</li>
        <li>
          Support for ARIA attributes with <code>ariaLevel</code> and <code
            >ariaLabel</code
          > props
        </li>
        <li>
          Optimal line height and character spacing for enhanced readability
        </li>
        <li>Hyphenation support for better text wrapping</li>
        <li>Maximum width options to maintain optimal reading line lengths</li>
        <li>Screen reader compatible with proper heading hierarchy</li>
      </ul>
      <div
        class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-500/10 p-4"
      >
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-200">
          <strong>Best Practice:</strong> Use semantic heading levels (<code
            >h1</code
          >-<code>h6</code>) to create a logical document structure. Avoid
          skipping heading levels and ensure there's only one <code>h1</code> per
          page. Use <code>maxWidth="prose"</code> for optimal reading experience
          on wide screens.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
